<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 94 / Chancellor denies prejudicing defence in arms to Iraq trial
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Kenneth Clarke told the Scott inquiry yesterday he was convinced he had
served the national interest by attempting to restrict information on
Britain's intelligence services from the Matrix Churchill trial about the
export of arms to Iraq.
The chancellor, pictured arriving at the inquiry, gave a robust performance.
He insisted that his actions had not prejudiced the defence in the trial and
refused to accept any personal blame.
