<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 94 / London Stock Exchange: Switch lifts Bowater
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The paper and packaging sector suffered the effects of a shift in funds
after UBS, the Swiss-owned securities house, advised investors to switch
holdings from Bunzl to Bowater. The former dipped 4 to 178p while the latter
resisted the overall market trend to rise 7 1/2 to 483 1/2 p.
The Swiss house argued that, after a fall of 40p over the past month,
Bowater was on an undeservedly low market rating. It told clients that the
company was a recovery stock with long-term growth prospects and had made
acquisitions in 'some above-average growth markets'.
Alternatively, UBS believes that Bunzl's share price has already taken on
board the recovery in paper prices and that the company needs to make both a
rights issue and acquisitions if it is to maintain its premium rating.
