<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 94 / World Commodities Prices: Coffee rise meets resistance -
Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COFFEE prices rose again at the London Commodity Exchange yesterday. The May
futures position edged up to resistance at Dollars 1,250 a tonne before
backing off Dollars 1 by the close, still up Dollars 6. Traders said
sentiment was still friendly although some thought the market looked
overbought and that producer selling might be attracted .
The COCOA market cautiously embraced Friday's strong gains in New York,
which were attributed to chart-inspired fund buying. By the close the May
position was Pounds 13 higher at Pounds 932 a tonne, having eased from an
earlier peak of Pounds 937.
Traders said the US jump was primarily a short-covering rally and predicted
more sober gains for London. 'We'll probably consolidate here, we don't have
the spec interest,' one said.
Compiled from Reuter
