<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Wills ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wills Group, the distributor of fluid handling equipment, reported doubled
pre-tax profits of Pounds 575,000 for the six months to January 1, against
Pounds 287,000.
The result was achieved on turnover up 44 per cent from Pounds 8m to Pounds
11.5m.
Wills also announced a further acquisition with the purchase of Cellar
Services Technology, a Manchester-based supplier to the brewing industry,
for Pounds 60,000.
In the year to May 31 it made pre-tax profits of Pounds 64,000 on turnover
of Pounds 1.5m.
The figures were the first to include a full contribution from Platon,
acquired in April last year. At the beginning of November, SRL, based in
Lyon, was acquired helping the French activities to show a good performance.
In Italy buoyant results in some areas balanced downturns inothers. Trading
in Germany and the Netherlands was poor, while in the UK there has been some
sign of improving market conditions but this has yet to show through in
significant increases in demand. Earnings per share improved to 0.36p
(0.28p) basic. or 0.35p (0.24p) fully diluted.
The interim dividend is raised from 0.1p to 0.115p.
</TEXT>
