<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 94 / UK Company News: London Industrial downturn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London Industrial, the property investment group which came to the market in
December, reported a fall in pre-tax profits from Pounds 363,200 to Pounds
182,200 for the quarter to December 31, bringing the total for the nine
months to Pounds 537,200 against Pounds 799,700.
Turnover on continuing operations improved to Pounds 1.71m (Pounds 1.52m)
for the three months. Earnings per share were reduced to 2.1p (6.3p).
In addition to five acquisitions during the period, an industrial estate was
bought for Pounds 164,000 from the London Borough of Southwark.
