FT  21 FEB 94 / Business Travel (Travel Update): Duty free
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EU finance ministers last week raised duty free allowances for travellers
coming to and travelling within the EU. Under rates which come into force on
April 1, travellers arriving from non-EU countries will be allowed to bring
in duty-free goods worth 175 European currency units (Dollars 195), almost
four times the current limit of 45 Ecus. For travellers between EU states
the limit will doubled to 90 Ecus.
