FT  21 FEB 94 / Save &amp; Prosper to cut card rate
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Save &amp; Prosper, the investment house, is to cut the interest rates on its
Visa card to below 1 per cent from the beginning of March, Andrew Jack
writes.
The charge of 0.95 per cent a month, which equates to annualised interest of
13.9 per cent, is believed to be the lowest rate charged since credit cards
were launched in the late 1960s. Save &amp; Prosper caused a stir in the sector
last September when it launched its credit card at rates substantially below
the industry average.
The investment house said: 'This is to show that we react to cuts in
interest rates and are much more responsive than the larger issuers.'
