<HEADLINE>
FT  19 FEB 94 / US and NZ upgrade relationship
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEORGE GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US has decided to restore senior level contacts with New Zealand,
thawing a seven-year chill between the two nations over New Zealand's ban on
visits by nuclear warships, writes George Graham in Washington. US defence
obligations under the ANZUS treaty will remain suspended.
</TEXT>
<XX>
